<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.172811>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. A paratype of Carlia caesius n. sp., dorsolateral aspect, male in life, BPBM 21157." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/172811/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.172815>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Distribution of sample localities [left] and Carlia fusca complex species [right] in Papua­Indonesia. Sample localities: 1, Ayamaru; 2, Manokwari; 3, Fak­Fak; 4, Tanah Merak; 5, Saengga; 6, Mandiwa; 7, Yeretina; 8, Gariau; 9, Unipo; 10, Uta; 11, Freeport; 12, Lorentz River; 13, Agats; 14, Bayum." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/172815/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.172812>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Juveniles of Carlia caesius (BPBM 21195 [left], BPBM 21203 [right]), dorsolateral aspect, preserved." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/172812/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

